The paper deals with secret key generation in a network model, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The model also involves communication between terminals, which falls under distributed computing (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes an algorithm for secret key generation, which involves combinatorial optimization (cs.SI).
